      "writtenOn": "2016-12-08T02:38:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m skeptical that this will work as intended. The first request will get the 25 most-recently-modified tasks, but other tasks might be modified before we make the next request. Those newly-modified tasks would then end up before the cursor, and wouldn\u0027t be returned at all.\n\nIt\u0027s more likely to work if we make a single request, specifying a Limit of say, 1.1 * the number of tasks we expect to be running, and if we underestimate the Limit, make additional requests with exponentially larger Limits.\n\nOr, after \"break mainLoop,\" recursively call GetModifiedTasks(pool, tasks[0].ModifiedTs) until there are no new tasks returned. (Except, don\u0027t use recursion and give up after looping N times.)",
      "revId": "10b0ac98b573dc22c08aeaa088623e77a0b32b14",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
